In commercial real estate from 2010 to 2015, China invested $17.1 billion, however with a growth rate of 70%, the article continues.It’s an extraordinarily high growth rate.It’s not going to stop, but the growth rate will slow down, and that should start happening in the next year or so,” Margon observed.In the past five years, Chinese investors spent over $100 billion on U.S. real estate, an amount that’s expected to double by year 2020, according to an article by Alexandra Pacurar for Commercial Property Executive.A recent study by the Asia Society and Rosen Consulting Group showed that from 2010 to 2015, China invested $93 billion in residential real estate, with a spending growth rate of 20%, according to the article.